ering services should be done internally and when it should be outsourced on DCS, Drives, PLC and other electrical equipment. Ensure a safe and healthy work environment through the compliance to legal regulations and mill procedures. Ensure that the electrical department and contractors comply in all respects with the relevant regulations. Effectively direct, electrical engineering and project team members, in terms of performance management, talent management, goal alignment, career development and learning. Accountable for selected Capex cost control and effectiveness as per Capex application. Assist commercial with contract negotiations for contracts. The ideal candidate should have: 4 Year B. Degree in Sciences or Engineering or National Higher Diploma in Engineering, with Recognition of Previous Learning or experience. Government Certificate of Competence \u2013 Factories. Relevant management qualification. Registration as a professional engineer would be advantageous. Relevant experience 8-10 years. Pulp and Paper Industry experience advantageous. CLOSING DATE: 17 July 2020 How to Apply? Please click on one of the buttons below. If you encounter any issue while applying contact your HR contact . Feel free to visit our website for further information www.sappi.com Sappi is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. Should you not have been contacted within 14 days of the closing date of this advert, please consider your application unsuccessful. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Priv